The paper deals with compressed sensing and recovery of images, which is a topic covered in several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper focuses on the development of efficient algorithms for robust compressed sensing. The second likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper deals with image recovery from compressed data. The third likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper uses robust statistics and regularization techniques to improve compressed sensing. The fourth likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia), as the paper deals with image recovery from compressed data, which is a multimedia application. The fifth likely category is cs.SI (Signal Processing), as the paper deals with signal recovery from compressed data.
